title: Area Cross Country: Mid-County boys 2nd in conference
text: Posted Oct. 8, 2015 at 10:14 PM Posted Oct. 8, 2015 at 10:14 PM KEWANEE — The Mid-County boys cross country team took second and Ridgewood finished fourth at the Lincoln Trail Conference Meet on Thursday. The Cougars scored 36 points to finish a mere one point behind first-place Mercer County’s 35. Annawan/Wethersfield was third with 64, the Spartans scored 99 and Princeville rounded out the field in fifth with 131. Caelin Foley won the meet with a time of 16:06. Kyle Campagna was sixth in 16:46.5 followed by Mike Bersell in seventh in 16:49.5 and Isaac Williamson in ninth in 16:50.2. Trenton Niemeyer finished out Mid-County’s scoring with a 17th-place time of 18:38.7. The Spartans were led by Andrew Hand with a 15th-place time of 18:25.4. Cameron Woodbury crossed the line in 16th in 18:30.0. Anthony Brown took 21st in 18:54.0, Evan Sullivan was 27th in 19:37.9 and Jordan Francis took 31st in 20:03.3. Freeman Shoemaker led West Central with a fourth-place time of 16:40.8. Adam Burnett placed 32nd with a time of 20:13.2 to lead United. On the girls side, Ridgewood took third with 94 points, Mid-County was fourth with 116 and United finished sixth with 155. Annawan/Wethersfield won the meet with 20, Mercer County was second with 44 and Princeville took fifth scoring 127. Makenna Medley set the pace for the Spartans with an 18th-place time of 22:44.7. Carlie Barman was 19th in 22:45.2 and Lauren Curry took 21st in 22:51.2. Tobi Matter placed 22nd in 22:53.3 and Emma Steider was 25th in 23:04.4. Lauren Hawes finished in 20:59.1 for 12th place to lead the Cougars. Kelly Harrell was 15th in 21:43.8 and Annadoria Ledbetter was 34th in 25:00.2. Alyssa Ingles finished in 36th with a time of 25:28.5 and Lisa McClay finished out Mid-County’s scoring with a 37th-place time of 26:09.1. United was led by Carolina Cruz with a time of 24:01.5 to finish in 30th-place. Olivia Bishop finished 32th in 24:45.9, Riley Davin was 35th in 25:23.5, Claire Gregory had a time of 28:33.2 for 42nd and Sara Simpson crossed the line in 29:51.0 for 43rd-place for the Red Storm.
